- title: Designing Design by Kenya Hara
  url: https://bookshop.org/p/books/designing-design-kenya-hara/636318?ean=9783037784501
  info: “Hara impresses upon the reader the importance of “emptiness” in both the visual and philosophical traditions of Japan, and its application to design, made visible by means of numerous examples from his own work”

- title: Atomic Design by Brad Frost
  url: https://atomicdesign.bradfrost.com/
  info: The design system book.

- title: The Timeless Way of Building by Christopher Alexander
  url: https://www.abebooks.com/9780195024029/Timeless-Way-Building-Alexander-Christopher-0195024028/plp
  info: One of the great books on design patterns, with an emphasis on a special type of quality that makes things feel alive.

- title: A Pattern Language by Christopher Alexander
  url: https://www.abebooks.com/9780195019193/Pattern-Language-Towns-Buildings-Construction-0195019199/plp
  info: In part 2 of his series on design patterns, Alexander presents one possible pattern language, through a series of examples of patterns that contribute to thriving homes, neighborhoods, and towns.

- title: Entangled Life by Merlin Sheldrake
  url: https://bookshop.org/p/books/entangled-life-how-fungi-make-our-worlds-change-our-minds-shape-our-futures-merlin-sheldrake/12072841
  info: On the surface, this is a book about fungi, but it is ultimately about connected systems, individuality, patterns, and scale. An endlessly fascinating read.

- title: Future Ethics by Cennydd Bowles
  url: https://bookshop.org/p/books/future-ethics-cennydd-bowles/9235560?ean=9781999601911
  info: “Future Ethics is an intelligent, quietly provocative book that challenges technologists stand up for change, and teaches essential ethical principals and methods for building a fairer future.”

- title: Ruined by Design by Mike Monteiro
  url: https://bookshop.org/p/books/future-ethics-cennydd-bowles/9235560?ean=9781999601911
